# echo.scenario — proves record.Open + emission sites + the recorder
# replay buffer compose end-to-end. new-session emits pane.ready while
# spawning the shell; the subsequent wait runs in a fresh connection
# whose subscriber is registered after that emission already fanned
# out. Replay re-delivers the event from the ring so the wait returns
# immediately.
#
# What this scenario deliberately does NOT do:
#
#   - `client at` + explicit `client kill` — wiring those into this
#     fixture surfaces a pre-existing race between command-path
#     options.Unset and pump-path register(), because Options guards
#     its map only by "all callers are the main goroutine" and the
#     synthetic-client plumbing breaks that assumption. Fixing the
#     race belongs to a later piece; this scenario sidesteps it by
#     staying on the read-only attach path.

new-session
wait pane.ready
